  "version": "2.0",
  "pipeline_stage": "validated",
  "title": "MetaRDK",
  "description": "MetaRDK is a stereo-electroencephalography (sEEG) dataset from pharmacologically intractable epilepsy patients performing a perceptual decision-making task with metacognitive confidence judgments. Participants discriminated the direction of random dot motion while providing confidence ratings, with neural recordings capturing high-gamma activity (70-150 Hz) throughout task performance. This dataset enables investigation of neural mechanisms underlying evidence accumulation, decision confidence, and changes of mind in human intracranial recordings.",
  "methods_description": "High-gamma activity (average power modulation in five non-overlapping frequency bands between 70-150 Hz) was recorded from implanted sEEG electrodes using a Micromed recording system at 512 Hz sampling rate. Data were segmented from trial onset (start button click) to trial offset (post-confidence response). Trials and channels with high epilepsy-related artifact were removed. Behavioral data including stimulus onset, response times, and confidence judgments were recorded for each trial.",
